==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek [[οπλίτης]] (heavily armed foot-soldier), from [[όπλον]] (arms, armor, weapon). Cf. Latin [[hoplomachus]] (gladiator).

===Noun===
'''hoplite''' (''plural:'' '''hoplites''')

#A heavy-armed infantry soldier of Ancient [[Greece]].

